inn1.comm: straight to the catcher but on the bounce, short outside off, punched off the back foot to short cover

big appeal for lbw, came back in sharply, Sibanda bent low and offered no stroke, was rapped on the pads just outside the line but it doesn't matter because he offered no shot, looked mighty close, it may have just missed off but that was certainly worth a shout
he's looking rusty here, walked well across the line to work it behind square, was lucky to get a slight inside edge onto his pads
straying on the pads, tries to glace it fine but isn't able to connect, it brushes the pads and he he gets a leg bye
shot off the pitch and came back in from middle, tried to whip it through midwicket but was struck hard on the thighs, another leg bye
gets some bat to it, finally, angling in towards middle and leg, turned away wide of square leg for a couple of runs
swinging away, decent start, shaping away from the right hander, lands on a good length, he lets it go
drawing him forward, pitching it up just outside off, guided it behind point for a quick single
leaving the right hander, gets forward, watches it close and leaves it be
reached for it there, much fuller, almost in the blockhole outside off, Sibanda tried to dig it out square but didn't get his bat down in time

bizzare, really bizzarre, Sibanda's embarrassed himself here! Left his leg stump alone, huge shuffle towards middle and it's pitched up on leg with a hint of inward movement, he offers no shot thinking it'll slide down the leg side but hears the death rattle, the leg stump's out of the ground and Sibanda's inclusion has failed to deliver
good bowling, in the channel outside off, trying to tempt the batsman into playing the drive and getting it to move away, left alone to the keeper
back of a length just outside off, cut it away straight to point, should have smacked it hard, it was a hit-me ball
slightly short on middle and off, punched off the back foot to mid-off where a fumble allows them a single
overpitched on the off but Coventry's not tempted, restraining himself to defend it solidly to cover
straying on the pads, tries to tickle it fine, is struck high on the pads and it rolls down to fine leg, they get a couple
darted back in sharply from a good length on middle,  was surprised by the movement was Coventry as he tried to work it square, was struck high on the pads, another leg bye
slightly short on middle and off, moves back and taps it down to midwicket
playing away from his body there, fending for one that's slightly wide, it moved away and he played at it from the crease with no footwork, just evaded the outside edge
beaten again! Angling in from wide of the crease, hitting just short of a good length on the off and shooting away as Coventry tries to defend it off the back foot, impressive start by Mahmud

Coventry's gone! The swing's doing the trick for Mahmud, pitched up outside off, had frustrated Coventry so far and the batsman went for flowing drive through mid-off, it moved away to kiss the outside edge and Mushfiqur hurled himself to his right to snap a sharp one, the record-holder's been dismissed for a duck
short of a good length on middle, rocks back and defends it cautiously back to the bowler
slightly short outside off, got right back and angled it down to third man to get off the mark
edged again, but didn't go at it hard, overpitched just outside off, tried to defend it straight but inside the line, runs down to third man, wide of second slip, for a single
back of a length on middle, punched straight to short cover
coming back in this time, fends it away to short midwicket
swinging in from a good length on middle, tried to force it past midwicket but was again struck on the pads, got an inside edge probably, called a run
first confident shot of the day, short and wide, cut away hard past point, well wide of third man, for a boundary
lands on a good length on the off stump, gets front and across and guides it behind point for a single to third man
he goes after it, senses a chance with a short one on middle, Masakadza rocks back and smacks it hard over midwicket for a boundary
lands on a good length outside off and moves away, left alone to the keeper
short of a good length a fraction outside off, punched to cover off the back foot
slightly short on middle, walks across to work it behind square, he's struck high on the pads, they get a single
pitched up outside off, driven hard and straight to mid-on
sliding in towards off from wide of the crease, watches it close onto his bat and guides it just behind point, third man is a little wide and steals the second
well fielded at mid-on as it was slapped back hard, he dived to his left and kept them down to a single
tucks him up for room by bowling it dead straight, he knocks it hard down the pitch
angles it towards the pads and he works it hard down to mid-on who moves to his right to intercept it
well bowled, straight again, he gets forward and defends back to the bowler
pokes his bat out to a delivery which angles away from him and nearly offers an edge
gets behind the line and deftly tucks it away wide of short fine leg
slower delivery and he gets well forward and angles it to third man, Mushfiqur bellows "keeper"!
seemed like a desperate heave but the placement was good enough to beat mid-on fairly comfortably
moves away from him slightly and he lunges forward and nearly feathers an edge
cramps him for room and he defends down the pitch and nearly inside edges it to the pads
he likes that on side, Mahmud drops it slightly short and Masakadza fetches it from outside off and biffs it well wide of mid-on
gets beside the line and taps it down to the covers
had to hurry there, he whips a full delivery hard to mid-on but doesn't bisect the gap,  the fielder has a shy at the stumps at the bowler's end

nice timing on that one, not too much width but he adjusts well and thumps it off the meat of the bat and bisects the gap between mid-off and cover, plays from the crease and boy that must have felt good

run out, Masakadza's fun stops here, Rasel changes the pace and Masakadza gets forward and angles it down to short third man, no realistic chance of a single but the batsman sets off, there's confusion in the calling and he turns around and makes a desperate attempt to make his ground, Ashraful fires the throw to Mushfiqur and the third umpire confirms the run out
impeccable timing from Williams, he gets a bit of width outside off and plays from the crease, punches it past the gap at point and the ball speeds away
stays behind the line and defends solidly back to the bowler
shuffles and clips it down to the on side
bowls it straight and he softly knocks it back to the bowler

timber! Superb delivery, the inswinger this time. Pitched on a good length outside off and Waller reached forward to defend it into the off side, it darted back in to beat him through the gate and crash into the stumps, Zimbabwe are sliding here
on target straightaway, targeting middle and off, just a hint of away movement, defended with a straight at just wide of the bowler
shortish on middle and leg, turned wide of midwicket from the crease, a lot of hesitation in calling there but no damage done, single completed easily in the end
Willaims chases that one, was too wide for him to go for it, just  swung hard at it, aiming to crash it through the covers but missed, given a wide though
harmless this time, short of a length outside off, Williams doesn't bother chasing it
swung in from outside off to crash into his thighs, would have been sliding down but the movement's having them in all sorts of trouble here
short and wide, it's the zone for Williams who cuts it away between point and cover for a boundary, he favours that area, got off the mark in a similar fashion
swinging in from middle towards leg, turned away towards midwicket
short of a good length on middle, Mushfiqur can't stop chattering, gets a little irritating sometimes but all wicketkeepers do that, punched to mid-off
back of a length, he latches onto it quickly, dismisses that hard through the covers from the crease, stood tall as he struck it, four more
shortish on middle, pushed off the back foot to mid-on
straying on the pads, helps it on its way to fine leg for a single
over the wicket to the left hander, straightish delivery on middle, defended rock solid back to the bowler
beaten, Mahmud continues to bother them, not much movement this time but just a tiny bit, pushes at it with little intent and is unable to connect
sliding down leg this time, a rare error from the bowler, given a wide
slightly short on middle, rocks back, closes the face and knocks it down to midwicket
Chigbumbura's lucky! Short on middle, held up a little and Chigumbura was too early in trying to turn it into the leg side, gets a leading edge and it lands safe between mid-on and mid-off
pitched up outside off, driven hard to mid-off on the front foot
pulls off his favourite shot, it's short and wide and cuts it hard but straight to point
shot up from a good length on the off, rocked back, stood tall and punched it towards deep cover for a single
slightly short on leg stump, whipped away through square leg, a yawning gap in the deep on the leg side and they get an easy three
bowled on a driving length outside off, cracked it straight to cover
slower one this time, he picked it, watched it onto his bat and dropped it down towards point
shot, but straight to the fielder, overpitched outside off and he leans into a drive, stroking it straight to cover
sliding on the leg stump, worked away just wide of short fine for a quick single

gone! Rasel's struck, Williams goes, the inswinger, short of a good length outside off and cut back in sharply, Williams rocked back to punch it towards mid-on but was done in by the movement, was rapped on the pads in front of the off stump, the umpire had no hesitation and he's made the right call
moving in from a good length on the off, driven straight down to mid-on
nicely done, banged in short on middle, pulled away hard behind square struck firmly and earns the boundary, he'll play his natural game

Dolar gets his fourth! Angling in towards middle from slightly wide of the crease, came half-forward and tried to close the face with bat perilously close to his pads to play it into the leg side, missed and was struck plumb in front
lands on a good length on middle, pushed back to the bowler
back of a length this time, rocks back and punches it straight to mid-on
played it well there, was surprised a little by the bounce but dropped his hands and kept it down while playing it to cover
trying to get it to move back in towards middle, gets forward, covers it well and taps it towards mid-on
slightly short on middle, kept a little low but Taylor watched it well, getting his bat down in time to tap it back to the bowler
overpitched on the off stump, gets forward and defends it to cover
classy, pitched up, there to drive, there isn't much power involved there, just pure timing, eased into the drive and placed it perfectly between cover and mid-off
swung back in, he didn't expect it to, played down the wrong line as he came forward to defend and was struck on the thighs, would have gone over
pitched up just outside off and getting it to move in, Utseya defends it hard towards cover
short of a length, holding its line, Utseya's not taking any risks, leaves it be
angling in towards middle, gets forward and slightly across to defend it back to the bowler
pitched up but it took off once it landed, well outside off, held its line, left alone to the keeper
drawing him forward, held it back just slightly, defended solidly towards cover
back of a length on the off, punched hard towards cover from the crease
drifting in towards middle and leg, would have slid down as he came forward to defend but was struck on the pads
gave it a bit of air this time, got to the pitch and defended it into the leg side
slightly short on the off, rocked back and defended it back to the bowler
fired in on middle, gets forward and worked it away towards midwicket
slightly short, much slower through the air, rocked back and pushed it hard to mid-off
flighted it just a fraction outside off, got to the pitch and tried to guide it with an angled bat towards point, got an inside edge onto his pads, a maiden
tossed up on middle, gets forward and defends it straight to cover, round the wicket to the right hander
short on leg stump this time, turned away wide of short fine for a single

Taylor's sensed a chance and he takes it, the wickets have had little impact on his style of play, the mid-on is up and he takes the bait, dancing down the pitch and chipping it over that fielder for a boundary
slightly short on middle, punched down to long-on for a single, sensible stuff
fired in short on middle, worked away behind square for a single to keep the strike
tosses it up outside off, driven through the line to extra cover
short on middle, punched off the back foot to midwicket
held it back slightly, threw it up, pushed back to the bowler off the front foot

dropped, Dolar the culprit, Shakib had kept him quiet and Utseya lost his patience, came down the track to dismiss that tossed-up delivery over midwicket, swung across the line, got a top edge and Dolar just had a few paces back to cup that but made a mess of it
threw it up again, lands on a good length on middle and off, gets a massive stride forward and defends it with bat close to pads
flights it on leg stump from round the wicket, worked in front of square for a quick single
tossed up outside off, square-driven hard wide of deep point for a couple of runs
quicker one bowled full outside off, driven down to mid-off for a single
threw it up outside off, bunts it down towards point
flighted on middle, closes the face and turns it through square leg for a single
lands full on the off, driven down to mid-off for a single to keep the strike
fired in straight on middle,. whipped away through square leg for a single
tossed up outside off, gets forward, to the pitch and defends
pushed away off the front foot just in front of square leg for a single
defended solidly, on the off stump, gets a stride forward and plays it to cover
flighted on middle, lunges forward and dabs it into the leg side
tossed up on the off, reaches forward and plays it back to the bowler
slightly short on middle and off, punched off the back foot down to mid-on for a single
Utseya gives him the charge but keeps it down, bunts it down to long-on for one more
flatter, just a margin outside off, closes the face and pushes it back to the bowler
appeared to stop on him a little, fullish outside off, checked his shot and pushed it towards long-on
flighted outside off, gets forward and plays it towards point
slightly short outside off, drops it short of point and calls for a single but it's not there, has been rightly sent back
slightly short on middle, worked away just wide of midwicket and calls for a single, he makes it easily even as there's a direct hit at the striker's end
flighted on middle, rocks forward and dabs it towards cover
shortish on middle, defended off the back foot to the bowler
fired in on middle and leg, held its line and rapped him on the pads, would have been sliding down
goes after it this time, it's tossed up outside off, charges down and swings it away over midwicket for a boundary, had consumed too many dot balls and finally got it to the ropes
spun in towards middle, turned it towards short fine
that's disappeared, it's in the slot, flighted, charges forward, takes it from a length and with a free swing of the arms, clears midwicket by a mile, powerfully struck
flatter and a little quicker this time, worked away to square leg
waiting for it to turn in and closing the face gently, finds short fine again
full outside off, drilled down the ground to long-on for a single
threw it up on the off, gets forward and taps it down to cover
tossed up outside off, driven in front of mid-on for a quick single
turned away from a good length on middle, defended towards point
banged in short on middle, long hop, rocks back, picking the length early and pulls it away hard wide of deep square leg for a boundary
fuller, gets to the pitch and taps it down to cover
four more, generally they've been harsh on the bad balls despite the wickets, short on the off, rocks back and pulls it hard over midwicket
tosses it up outside off, Utseya lunges forward and drops it towards cover
flighted on middle, driven straight to midwicket
places it into the gap between square leg and midwicket for a quick run
flattish on middle, presents the full face as he plays it back to the bowler
threw it up on middle and leg, charged down the track and cracked it down to long-on for a single
bowled on a length on the off stump, pushed back to the bowler
pitched up on middle and leg, drives it down towards long-on for a single
bowled flat on middle, defended towards midwicket off the front foot
shortish on middle, spun away just a hint, followed it and tapped it down to cover
found the gap, just a fraction short outside off, got forward and cut it between short third man and point for two more, brings up the 50-partnership
short on middle, pushed back to the bowler on the back foot
back of a length on middle, punched to long-on for one more
sliding it into the pads from round the wicket, tried to force it through the leg side but was rapped on the pads, would have gone down
stifled appeal but that went off the pads, spun in and struck the flap, lobbed up and Mushfiqur pouched it
straightish on middle and leg, worked away through square leg for a single
pitched up outside off, charges down the track and bunts it down to long-off for a single
back of a length on middle, pushed through to midwicket
shortish on leg stump, whips that through the square-leg region for one more
bowled'im! Poor shot, that. Tossed up, lands on a good length on middle and spins in sharply towards leg, goes for the pull when the shot wasn't really on, misses and is bowled.
shortish on middle from round the wicket, punched back to the bowler
turned away from short of a length outside off, dabbed towards point
hurled it down the leg side, didn't get it to spin, called a wide
flighted on middle and off, defended towards midwicket
tossed it up this time, bowled full on middle and off, Taylor got a stride forward, seemed as it he played down the wrong line and was struck on the pads, it was the stride that saved him
fired in short on middle and leg, struck on the pads as he tried to whip it square, would have slid down
flattish on middle, tries to defend it straight, it turns in to take a thick inside edge wide of square leg
short on middle, worked away wide of midwicket for a single
flattish on the off stump, pushed back to the bowler
fullish on middle, pushed wide of the bowler
shortish on middle this time, pushed through the line wide of the bowler, some lethargic fielding allows them to complete a single
flighted outside off, gets front and across and drives it to midwicket
tossed up outside off, drilled hard but straight back to the bowler
slightly short on middle, defended to cover from the crease
pitched up on middle and off, defended back onto the pitch
pitched up outside off, driven through the line to cover
short outside off, held its line and he let it go
beauty, much slower through the air, tossed up on the off and turned away sharply, beaten as he came forward to defend
flighted on middle, driven through the line to mid-on
tries to relieve the pressure a little, comes down the track and heaves it hard wide of long-on but doesn't quite get the timing right, kept down to two
short on middle and leg, pushed off the back foot to long-on for one more
tossed up outside off, turned away to square leg
tossed up on the off, driven down to long-on for a single
dropped it short on middle, just a hint of spin, punched to midwicket from the crease
tossed up outside off, taken on the full and driven hard down to long-off
overpitched on middle, presents the straight bat and bunts it down to long-on
pitched up, driven uppishly but short of cover
hurled it flat on middle, defended into the leg side towards midwicket
pitched up on middle, driven straight to mid-on, striking it reasonably well but is not able to pinch the singles
that's the best solution, flighted on middle, gets forward, bends low and slog-sweeps it hard over midwicket for a boundary
quick through the air, bowled short on leg stump, turned down to square leg, single taken
kept a little low, lands on a good length on middle, worked away to midwicket
flighted on middle, pitched up, driven elegantly down to midwicket
short on the off stump, punched off the back foot wide of the bowler, cut off by midwicket
looping it just outside off, gets forward and taps it down to point
lands on a length on middle, knocked back hard but straight to the bowler, time for drinks
flighted it outside off, driven hard wide of a diving extra cover towards long-off for a single
slightly short on the off, pushed to cover from the crease
flighted outside off, cracked down the ground to long-on for a single
flatter on middle, comes down the track, presents the full face and gets that past the bowler for a single
short on the off, pulled away, lands just short of deep square leg for a single
pitched up on middle, driven down to long-on for a single
shortish on middle, punched to midwicket off the back foot
quick single, guided it just wide of point and Rice called to complete the single well in time
pitched up on middle, thumped it back down the ground to long-on
short of a length on middle, played away straight to midwicket
threw it up outside off, cracked it hard down the ground into the V again
appeal for lbw, tossed up outside off, got across the line to work it into the leg side, it spun back in to rap him on the pads but he was struck outside the line
tossed up on middle, driven down the ground to long-on
pitched up on middle, whipped away slightly uppishly through midwicket for a single
spun in from middle, was struck high on the pads as he tried to turn it square
driven through the line just wide of midwicket but the fielder cuts it off to prevent the single
good running, pushed it gently into the vacant gap in the deep on the leg side, deep midwicket takes ages to come down and cut that off and they've taken two
Rasel's gifted them an extra run, tossed up on middle, driven just wide of long-off and Rasl doesn't pick it up cleanly while running in, two more
in the blockhole outside off, tries to close the face, gets an inside edge onto his pads
pitched up outside off, drilled down to long-on
quick through the air, short on the off, turned away to midwicket, there's no run on offer

now there is, in fact they've taken two, worked away gently into the deep square leg region and the fielder takes time to run in, completes his 14th ODI half-century, a solid, patient hand amid a lot of pressure
flighted outside off, driven hard between long-off and deep cover for a brace
hurled it short outside leg stump, poor ball, slapped it fine to earn four important runs
pulls off the reverse sweep, flighted outside off, gets it past short third man, over him in fact, four more to the score, spunky batting
sensible, gives Taylor the strike, turns it wide of midwicket for a single
slightly short on the off, gets forward and plays it back to the bowler
short on middle and leg, worked wide of short fine for  quick single
turned in from middle, spins down, gets struck on the pads as he tries to work it down
back of a length on middle, swatted down to deep midwicket for a single
pitched up outside off, driven down to long-on
flat through the air, comes back in from outside off, played back to the bowler
pitched up on middle, driven down the ground to long-on, rotating the strike well these two
hurled flat on middle and leg, turned away through square leg
pitched up on middle, closes the face again and gets it down to deep square leg for a single
pitched up outside off, driven straight to midwicket from the crease
hurled it wide of the batsman as he saw him coming down, had to reach for it while playing it to point
lands on a good length outside off, pushed to cover
short outside off, chopped down wide of cover for a single
short and wide, slaps it hard past deep cover for a couple more, Mushfiqur yells out an ear-shattering scream, shouting "keeper, keeper"
bowled short on middle, pulled down towards deep midwicket for one more

bowled flat from round the wicket, angled it in towards off stump and it spun away, Taylor went for the sweep, looking to play it through square leg but missed, was rapped on the pads and was given. Replays show it would have missed off, and he was struck outside the line, poor call
flat, bowled short outside off, spinning in, defended back to the bowler
shortish outside off, chopped down wide of cover for a single
back of a length on middle, swats it down to long-on for a single
shortish outside off, played towards midwicket off the back foot
held it back again, slapped it past the bowler to long-off
spinning in towards middle and leg, worked away to square leg
beaten, spun away sharply from a good length on the off, played inside the line there, trying to drive it straight but missed
excellent placement, bowled it short on the off, bent low and swept it really hard, bisecting the gap between deep square leg and deep midwicket for four more
shortish on the off, pushed off the back foot to cover
spun away after he bowled it flat and slightly quick from round the wicket, tried to drive through, was beaten by the spin
bowled on a length outside off, cracked wide of the bowler to long-off for a single
good turn, tried to ease it past point but is unable to connect as it zips away
short on middle, punched to midwicket off the back foot
shortish outside off, slapped down to long-on
short on middle, gets back and punches it down to long-on
lots of slaps and swats today, especially from Rice who seems to be an expert at killing flies, played down to long-on
spinning in from a good length outside off, pushed it straight to cover
angling it down, tried to paddle it down, got the top edge, there's no short fine so its safe, two more
fired it quick on middle, paddled it down to short fine who's just come in
flat outside off, tried to crash it through cover, didn't connect well, mistimed it to cover
cracked off the front foot wide of cover for a single
pitched up outside off and he accepts the invitation, rocking forward and swinging it hard over midwicket for a big six, a fighting knock this
keeps the strike by dabbing it wide of cover, nearing 200 now
full outside off, bunts it down to long-on for a single
good shot, picked his spot and smacked it, short outside off, waited for it to turn in, rocked back and crashed it through the gap between point and cover, brings up the 200, excellent recovery
stumped, comes round the wicket, fires it short outside off as he sees Cremer charging down, tries to slap it through cover, misses and Mushfiqur takes off the bails to find him well short
turning in sharply, over the wicket now, playing across the line, was struck slightly high, got a stride forward but was close
short on middle, punched to midwicket off the back foot
much slower through the air there, waited for it, got behind it and tapped it to midwicket
on target immediately, in the blockhole on middle, dug out wide of midwicket for a single
slower one bowled on a good length on leg stump, turned away wide of midwicket for a single
bowled short on middle and Price pulls off a beauty, shuffles across and scoops it over short fine for a valuable boundary

moved well across to scoop it over short fine again but was rapped on the pads, Sahiba gave him out but he actually wasn't as it struck him outside the line and would have missed off anyway, poor decision again

inn2.comm: shaping in to the left hander, short on middle, pushed off the back foot to midwicket
short of a length outside off, chopped down square into the deep, wide of third man, for a single
sliding down the leg side, moves well across, given a wide
lands on a good length outside off and moves away a touch, lets it go
fuller, trying to induce him into playing the drive, gets it to move away but Mushfiqur is taking no risks, leaves it be
pushed him back with a short one on middle, rocks back and defends it onto the pitch
good movement away from the batsman, short of a good length and Mushfiqur thinks of playing at it but withdraws his bat at the right time after watching it leave him
coming round the wicket, military medium, bowls it on a good length outside off, Tamim leaves it be
angling it in towards middle from round the wicket, defended straight to short cover
pitched out and he goes for the drive but sends it straight back to the bowler, the bat turned in his hand there

ooh, almost! good length outside off, moved back in and Tamim misjudged it, shouldering arms to that one, missed off stump by a whisker and Taylor fumbled it behind the stumps, failing to get his body behind the ball, concedes four byes
pitched up and he is sucked into the drive, strokes it well but straight to cover
short, coming back in, tries to cut it past point but mistimes it, ends up going much finer, towards third man, for a single
overpitched, inviting him to play the drive but Tamim is unable to pierce the field, drives it straight to Sibanda at cover who dives to his right to save a few runs
short of a good length outside off, rocks back and cracks it to extra cover from the crease
getting it to move in towards middle and off, driven with a full face to mid-off
short and wide, goes for the cut but it keeps a little low, fails to connect, zips past the outside edge
booming drive but again, straight to the fielder, must be frustrating, pitched up again and he connects it well but can't find the gap
much closer to the stumps this time, on a good length just a fraction outside off, defended back to the bowler
angling in towards off from over the wicket to the right hander, defended with ease to point
much fuller, gets forward, to the pitch, and pushes it firmly but straight to short cover
overpitched on middle, driven back past the bowler to mid-on
wristily done, a touch too straight this time, worked away through square leg for a well-run two, gets off the mark
fullish on middle, presenting the straight bat while driving it back to the bowler
short and wide, perhaps an element of frustration there, tries to clear point but is not able to connect
pitched up outside off, slashed away down to third man for a single
lands on a good length outside off, driven through the line to mid-off
much straighter, on middle this time, pushed back to the bowler
shot! That's class, pitched up on middle and off, takes a step forward and drives it elegantly over the bowler's head, wide of mid-off, for his first boundary
targeting the blockhole this time, dug out towards cover
back of a length on leg stump, tried to glace it down but was struck high on the pads, gets a leg bye
lands on a good length on middle, tight line, defended back to the bowler
shortish this time, waits for it, has plenty of time, drops it short of cover
no use, short and wide, Mushfiqur waited for it and slashed at the right time, cut it hard between point and that close-in fielder for another classy boundary
four more, poor delivery on the pads, clipped it away wide of the fine-leg fielder, who's a little too square, for a boundary, Mushfiqur's settling in nicely here
good running, drops it off the front foot short of mid-off and immediately calls, Tamim takes a while to respond but so does the mid-off fielder and they take a single
Tamim's looking a little scratchy, short and wide, goes for the cut, misses, kept a little low there
quick single, shaping into the right hander, pushes it firmly past the bowler to mid-off and calls again, made it well in time, had to rush through but would have been in had there been a direct hit
back of a length on middle, punched from the crease towards mid-on
short on leg stump, swung away to fine leg for a single, slower one, his 300th run of the series
too straight, closed the face and just eased it wide of mid-on for a single
short of a good length on the off, punched off the back foot to short cover
angling it in towards middle and off, forced through to midwicket, it's Mushfiqur who's dominated this stand so far
Mushfiqur goes big, overpitched, length ball outside off, swings it away comfortably over mid-on for a boundary
slower one bowled short on the off, got some good bounce there, tried to run it down but missed
back of a length on middle, rocks back and defends it onto the pitch
slower one bowled on a good length on the off, cuts back in, rocks back and knocks it past the bowler, short of mid-on, for a single
another mistimed shot, it's a poor delivery, short and wide, tries to crash it through cover but fails to get hold of it
well struck but straight to short cover, bowled on a length and he gets stuck into the drive but again, unable to get it past the circle

appeal for run out, fullish on the off, gets back and drops it short of mid-off and sets off for a single, a direct hit at the non-striker's end but Mushfiqur is well in, they get an extra run on the ricochet
shot! He's looking good, pitched up outside off, smashed it hard over the bowler's head, four more, came off the middle
goes for a big heave over midwicket this time, bowled on a good length outside off, tries to swing it hard but is unable to connect well, gets an inside edge on his pads
a legcutter gone bad, poor bowling combined with poorer keeping, slipped out of his hand, too wide and Taylor, who has enough time to have it covered, messes it up behind the stumps
back of a length on the off, punched back towards mid-off
short and wide, cut hard into the ground but straight to point
short of a length on leg stump, tries to whip it square, is struck hard on the thighs
strikes immediately! A lot of turn there for him, short outside off, spun back in sharply, Tamim rocked back to attempt the cut, missed it completely and was bowled
tossed up outside off, driven hard wide of long-off for a couple of runs, off the mark
pushed off the front foot through to long-off for a single
flighted on the off stump, takes it on the full and bunts it down to long-off
he's rushing is Ashraful, came down the track in an attempt to clear mid-on but miscued it over midwicket, just a single but that was unnecessary
tossed up outside off, lunges forward and defends it back to the bowler
short of a length on the off, punched down to cover off the back foot
landed short outside off, restrains himself from playing the cut, leaves it be

what a catch! An absolute stunner, bowled short and wide, goes for the cut, connects well but finds Sibanda at point who times his jump to perfection and plucks it out of thin air one-handed, tumbles but holds on, two down now
full and wide, goes for it, tries to drive it through cover but misses, it moves away and just escapes the outside edge
tossed up on middle from round the wicket, defended with a reach into the leg side
tossed up on middle, driven back to the bowler

good, positive cricket from Mushfiqur, undeterred by the two wickets, it's flighted, he gets to the pitch by dancing down the track and cracks it over the bowler's head, wide of long-off, for a boundary
delicately done, angling in on the off and spinning away, waits for it, bends low and cuts it behind short third for two more
flatter, on middle and leg, pushed off the front foot to midwicket
short on middle and leg, whipped away to square leg
bowled on a length outside off, gets forward and pushes it down to mid-off
back of a length outside off, cuts it between point and cover, no run on offer
slower one bowled short outside off, cuts it away square, wide of third man, for a couple of runs
angling it in, got a bit of inward movement there, tried to dab it down behind point but couldn't get his bat to it
pushed off the front foot to cover, lands on a good length and he punches it straight
tossed up outside off, leans forward to defend it to the cover-region
short on middle, rocks back to punch it down to mid-on, thinks of a single but it's not there
drifting in towards the right hander but it spins away, Mushfiqur gets forward to defend but it takes the outside edge, rolling wide of short third for a couple of runs
pitched up on middle, driven uppishly through midwicket for a single
Raqibul does this well, bowled short on middle, gets back and turns it wide of midwicket for a quick single, supported Tamim superbly in the previous game
pushed through to cover off the front foot
gets forward and bunts it down to cover again
slower delivery outside off, Mushfiqur latches onto it quickly, swings it away over midwicket for a boundary
pushed away off the front foot, slightly across the line, to midwicket
worked away down to fine leg for a single
short of a good length on the off, rocks back and drops it into the off side
tossed up on the off stump, defended with a reach
pitched up outside off, comes down the track and drives it inside out wide of long-off for a single
drifting in towards middle, gets forward and taps it into the off side
sliding it in towards middle, lands short, moves across and works it down to short fine
straight on middle, gets across the line and works it straight to midwicket
hurled it short on middle, whipped away straight to square leg, tidy over
starts off with a short one on middle, punched down to deep midwicket off the back foot, thought of the second but it's not available
poor fielding, lets it through his legs to the boundary, drilled down the ground straight to long-off and Masakadza embarrasses himself in the deep, four more
chopped down to short third man, short outside off
sweetly struck, it's tossed up on middle, he gets forward and chips it firmly wide of long-on for a one bounce four, landed just inside the ropes
gets forward and defends it solidly in front of the bowler
tossed up outside off, driven hard down the ground to long-off
angling in towards middle, defended back to the bowler from the crease
short on the off, pushed off the back foot to cover
threw it up on middle, rocked back and dropped it short on the off side
quicker through the air, full on middle, driven straight to extra cover
shortish on middle, punched off the back foot to midwicket
hurled in full on middle, defends it watchfully back onto the pitc
sliding on the pads, turned to midwicket from the crease, thinks of a single but is wisely sent back
short on middle, gets forward and turns it in front of square leg
gets on the back foot and works it between square leg and midwicket but can't squeeze the single

almost had him there, tossed it up, landed full outside off, sucked him into the drive, Mishfiqur went at it hard but got a thick edge as it turned away, in the air but well wide of point for three runs
drawing him forward, really slow through the air, Raqibul wasn't fully in control of that one, chipped it with little intent, landed safely in the direction of long-on
lands on a length on middle and leg, bunts it down to long-on
raises his 50, charges down the track and knocks it down to long-off, a well-paced innings and has made good use of his promotion up the order
fired in short on middle, worked away to square leg for a single
tossed up outside off, driven through the line to long-off for one more
firing it full on middle, lunges forward to tap it back onto the pitch
threw it up on middle, waited for it and at the last moment, dropped it on the off side
fullish on the off, gets forward and pushes it back to the bowler
makes some room for himself and tries to place it in the big gap between cover and point, gets a single
poor line, bowled it full outside off, Mushfiqur sweeps it down really fine, wide of the short-fine fielder, for three more
didn't spin, short on the off stump, rocked back and smashed it through that gap between cover and point for four runs
threw it up on middle, reaches forward and defends it back to the bowler
pitched it up on the off stump, drove it through the line to long-off for a single
shortish on middle, rocks back and punches it back to the bowler
flights it on middle and leg, driven straight to midwicket
angling it on middle, swept down to short fine
pushed through fuller, came down the track and tapped it back to the bowler
tossed it up on middle, came down the track while making a bit of room simultaneously, driven through to long-on
angling it in on middle, defended with a massive stride back to the bowler
spinning away after pitching on a good length outside off, plays it down to point
flights it on the middle, Raqibul gets forward and taps it down to cover
bowls it on a length outside off and gets it to turn away, nudges it wide of short third man
pushed through quick and straight on middle, gets front and across and turns it wide of midwicket for a single
flat again, on middle and off, tries to sweep it square but is a little early into the shot, is struck on the rib cage
held back the length, punched it back towards the bowler who fumbled it and allowed them to run through for a single
floats it up just outside off, gets forward and paddles it fine, wide of long leg, for a couple more
tossed up on the off, cracks it down to long-on for a single
full on the off, pushed through to cover on the front foot
pitched up on middle, driven down to long-on for a single
held it back slightly, came forward and dabbed it down to point

Raqibul departs, the bowling change works! Tossed it up well outside off, reached for it with a bug lunge and tried to paddle it down, all that hard work would have yielded just a run but this is worse, it catches the top edge and Waller takes the easiest of catches at short fine
pitched up on the off, gets across and drives it straight back to Cremer
pitched up on middle, digs it out towards midwicket
flatter and this one didn't turn, fullish on the off, gets forward and defends it on the leg side
lands full outside off, drives it hard down the ground to long-off, brings up the 100
on middle and leg, sweeps it square, gets it wide of long leg and calls for the second, Shakib is late to react but the throw is wayward and they get two
overpitched on middle, tries to drive it past the bowler but ends up getting an inside edge onto his pads
quickish on middle and leg, turned to midwicket
tossed up on middle, comes down and cracks it down to long-on for a single
threw it up outside off, charged down and got to the pitch, defended it to cover
comes down and drives it down to midwicket
short outside off, moves back and chops it down between point and cover for a single
threw it up again, came down and drove it hard to long-on, good flourish as well to back it up
shortish on the off stump, gets back and taps it back to the bowler

produces the leading edge, that's the googly, shortish on leg stump, the bounce as well as the turn took Shakib by surprise as he tried to nudge it behind square, lobbed up, fell well short of a short third running in
full on leg stump, whipped away through to deep square leg for A SINGLE
back of a length on middle, pulled away midwicket into the deep for one more
poor ball, sliding down the leg side, Shakib doesn't have to do much, just helps it on its way wide of short fine, sweeping it well, to earn his first boundary
gets forward, takes it on the full and drives it back to Cremer
short and wide, rocks back and cuts it straight to point
pitched up outside off, drive through the line to cover
full outside off, drives it hard wide of the bowler for a single to long-off
threw it up on middle, came down and worked it away to midwicket
pitched up outside off, takes it on the full and chips it towards long-off for a single
flighted outside off, cracked off the front foot straight to cover
flighted outside off and driven down the ground to long-off
tossed up on middle and leg, he gets on his knee and sweeps to deep square-leg
not afraid to give it a lot of air, easily pushed through the line to long-off
chips down the track but checks his shot, long-off is the place to hang out
tossed up on middle and leg, he works him down to long-on
tries to flick him across the line but the ball straightens and clips his pads outside the line of leg
gently tossed up outside off and swept away to deep midwicket
stays back and punches it right back to the bowler
pushes it down the ground to long-on
works it to long-on
stays back waits for the turn and pushes it past the bowler
tossed up outside off, he makes use of the width and slashes it past point
short and wide, cut away to deep point for a single
slower one bowled short outside off, took forever to get to him, tried to chop it down to third man, didn't make contact
short and wide, slashes it hard down towards deep point for a single
poor fielding, punches it to mid-off for a quick single but the fielder fumbles, had he picked it up cleanly and scored a direct hit, Shakib would have been in trouble
back of a length on middle, struck back down the ground wide of long-on for a single
slower one bowled short outside off, drags it down to midwicket
short outside off, turns back in, slaps it to cover off the back foot

chance of a catch, short and wide, tries to cut it hard, gets a bit of bounce that produces a thick edge, it was Waller at short third and he turned the wrong way initially, it went well over to his left and evaded his reach to roll down to the ropes
tosses it up outside off, bunts it down to long-off for a single
threw it up just outside off, came down the track and pushed it back to the bowler
slightly short on middle and leg, works it away through square leg for a single
starts off with a long hop outside off which is promptly punished, rocks back and pulls it really hard, wide of the diving deep midwicket for a boundary
back of a length again but it's punched straight to cover this time
low full toss on the off, cracked straight to cover from the crease
pitched up just a fraction outside off, driven down the ground to long-off
back of a length on the off, cut away hard to point
poor ball down the leg side, its a full toss, Mushfiqur didn't get his bat to it, Coventry didn't get his gloves to it and rolled down the fine-leg boundary
fullish outside off, pushed through to cover, calls for a single but is sent back
tossed up on middle and off, comes down the track and crunches it down to long-on for a single
short of a length outside off, smacked straight to cover
bowled it on a good length on the off, played back to the bowler
floating in towards middle, worked away to midwicket
full on middle and off, wrisitly drives it down to long-on for a single, they've added 50 now
pitched up, comes down the track and drives it inside out wide of long-off for a single to keep the strike
hurls it down the leg side, the keeper fumbles, they get two runs to the total
pitched up on middle, driven confidently down towards long-on for a single
short and wide, cuts it away wide of deep point, the fielder takes a while to cut it off and they get a couple more
full and wide, gets to the pitch and square-drives it past a diving point, wide of deep point, for a couple more
much straighter this time, lands on a good length on middle, tries to force it through cover but is unable to pierce the field
held back the length slightly, slaps it back straight to the bowler
banged in short, mistimes a pull to deep square leg for one more
shortish on middle, rocks back and punches it down the ground to long-on
angling it in towards middle, worked away through square leg for a single
flights it straight on leg stump, whips it down to deep square leg, another run
overpitched and gets the treatment, it's full and wide, a meaty delivery, Mushfiqur's eyes light up, gets forward to the pitch and creams it through the covers
tossed up just outside off, pushed back to the bowler
expensive over, this, short and wide, moves back to cut as it turns in, gets a thick outside edge wide of Waller at short third for another boundary
short and wide, flat trajectory, cut straight to point

Shakib's holed out! Cremer gave it some air, it was pitched up outside off, Shakib came down the track and tried to clear long-on, got quite a bit of bat on it but didn't get the desired elevation, landed safe in the palms of Masakadza in the deep
ooh, bowled short and straight, kept a little low, he got right back, waited for it and turned it away past midwicket for a single
angling it down the leg side, didn't get any spin there, called a wide
flighted on middle, gets forward to the pitch and drives it with a full face down to long-on
pitched up outside off, gave it a lot of air, drove it straight to cover
went on straight, Mahmudullah played for the turn, got a thick inside edge wide of midwicket for a quick single
slow through the air, bowled short on the off, punched back to the bowler
fullish on the off, leans forward and defends it on the pitch
threw it up this time, Mahmudullah is content, dabbing it to cover
angling in towards middle, defended with a straight bat towards extra cover
sliding in towards leg stump, worked to midwicket
kept really low, that was the arm ball, bowled short on middle, was fortunate to get his bat down in time while punching it to cover
short of a length outside off, cracked down to deep cover for a single
quicker on the off stump, pushed through to point off the back foot
slower through the air, bowled on a good length on the off, defended to the side of the pitch
flights on middle, worked away wide of midwicket, there's no single available
short on middle, whipped away off the back foot to deep square leg for a single
tossed up outside off, driven through the line to long-off for a single
tosses it up on the off stump, Mushfiqur drives it down to long-off for a single
went with the arm that one, short on the off, punched down to long-off for a single
short and wide, cracked off the back foot down to deep point for one more
shortish again, pushed off the back foot straight to cover
targeting the blockhole outside off, dug out wide of cover and rushes through for a single
slightly short outside off, slapped off the back foot straight to cover
poor fielding, short on leg stump, worked away wide of short fine, they get a single, a needless throw and the bowler fails to back it up, concedes another run
tossed up on the off, gets forward and taps it back to the bowler
slightly short on the off, spins away, punched down to long-off for a single
back of a length on leg stump, chipped down to deep midwicket for a single
quicker through the air, short on middle, pushed away to midwicket
threw it up, lands full on middle, defended into the leg side
short and wide, cut away straight to point
back of a length, a hint of inward movement off the pitch, moves away and runs it down to third man for a single
smacked it into the stands, he doesn't want to wait, hurled short outside off, rocked back and pulled it disdainfully over the deep-midwicket boundary, ferocious strike
straying on the pads, walks across and tickles it down to fine leg for a single
slower one bowled short on the off stump, punches it down the ground to long-on for a single
short and wide, knocks it down towards cover from the crease
angling it full on the off, comes down the track and drives it down to long-off
targeting middle and leg, pushed through to midwicket
straying on the pads, swept down behind square for a couple wide of long leg
slightly short on the off, moves back and drops it into the off side
firing it flat on middle, pushed back to the bowler
drifting into the right hander and spinning away, gets forward to defend, plays inside the line and gets a thick outside edge that lands safe
dropped it short on the off, punched down to long-off for a single
flighted on middle, moves to 98 with a drive down to long-off
firing it short on leg stump, turned down to short fine
tossed it up outside off, didn't turn, dabbed it down to point
spinning away from middle, whipped wide of midwicket for a single
hurled it short on leg stump, worked away to short fine from the crease
back of a length on middle, struck down towards long-on for a single
firing it down leg stump, turns it down to square leg
flights it just outside off, knocked down to cover

he misses out on a century! stumped, tossed it up outside off, Mushfiqur wanted to get it over and done with, charged out of his crease to loft it over the bowler's head, it turned away and Coventry clipped the bails to find him agonizingly short of a maiden ODI ton
arm ball, bowled quick, short on middle, chopped down to point
drifting in towards the off stump, turning away, gets on the back foot and defends it to cover
fired it on a good length outside off, defended to cover
short outside off, slashed hard, got a thick outside edge and it fell just short of Price at short third, he fumbled and they take two
went with the arm, bowled on a good length on middle, defended back to the bowler
sliding it on leg stump, worked away to midwicket
short and quick on the off, smacked down to long-on for a single
threw it up this time, very slow through the air, defended with a reach to cover
landed short outside off, pushed through to cover off the back foot
almost done, short outside off, comes down the track and swats it past the bowler wide of mid-off for a boundary
bouncer, we haven't seen any today, banged in outside off, left alone
short of a good length outside off, walks across and bunts it to point
pitched up on middle and off, flicks it away to deep square leg for a single
full toss on the off stump, stays rooted to the crease and punches it to mid-off
flighted on middle, drive straight to mid-off, how long will this take?
short on middle, punched off the back foot just wide of mid-off for a single
threw it up and invited him to go for the big one, swung hard but missed
full on middle, driven back to the bowler who hurls it back at the stumps at the striker's end
all over, tossed up on the off, waits for it, takes on a length and smashes it over the bowler's head to seal a 4-1 win
